    "created_at": "2013-10-22T17:50:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-10-22T17:50:56Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm -1 on this, and would prefer the consistency of always using .ipython if it exists, and allowing for .config/ipython for XDG fan-folks\n\nI don't understand who decided that XDG is a good idea, and why, and it's not even that widely used. I'm pissed at Matplotlib always barking at me about it. Why should one POSIX system behave so much different from all others? There's not a good reason. It's OK that some people want to use XDG, so we should allow them to, but FORCING everyone to use it is just wrong.\n\nI think it's stupid to make me have a different set of dot files on FreeBSD and on Debian.\n"
  },
