    "created_at": "2013-10-22T18:03:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-10-22T18:03:45Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm happy to make it more consistently `.ipython` if we prefer - I've argued against moving to `.config/ipython` enough myself. I'd just like something simple we can tell users about where their config files are.\n\nWe don't even use XDG properly - the files we save in the IPython directory are a mixture of at least Config and Data, with probably bits of Runtime and Cache information as well.\n\n(Though even the current scheme shouldn't differ between FreeBSD and Debian - we follow the XDG convention on all POSIX platforms except OS X)\n"
  },
